# =============================================================================
# Rust / Cargo
# =============================================================================
debug/
target/
# Cargo.lock IS committed for this workspace (it ships binaries).
# Committing it is required for:
#   * Reproducible builds (every dev + CI + release resolves the same graph)
#   * Supply-chain integrity (pairs with cargo-vet + cargo-deny pinning)
#   * SLSA attestation integrity (release provenance references a specific
#     dep graph; without Cargo.lock that graph would drift every run)
#   * cargo-vet stability (exemptions are keyed on specific crate-versions
#     - a floating Cargo.lock would break cargo vet check on every
#     unrelated upstream patch release)
# To deliberately update deps, use `cargo update` or a Dependabot PR.
**/*.rs.bk
*.pdb
# macOS `sed -i` backup files
*.toml-e
*.yml-e
*.rs-e

# =============================================================================
# Build artifacts & generated binaries
# =============================================================================
# build/ holds generated artifacts, including the go/ship pipeline logs
# (scripts/ci-pipeline writes build/logs/).
build/
*.rlib
*.bin
# `*.bin` keeps transient generated blobs out of git.  When the project
# gains INTENTIONAL committed binary assets (embedded tables via
# `include_bytes!`, integration-test fixtures), carve them back in here
# explicitly - a file that is both committed AND gitignored makes
# release-plz abort with "the working directory has uncommitted changes".
# Fixture carve-out (documented per fixture in tests/fixtures/README.md):
!tests/fixtures/**/*.bin
# Binaries are distributed via GitHub Releases, not committed to the repo
dist/
/vendor/

# =============================================================================
# Local scratch space (the ONLY blanket-ignored local area)
# =============================================================================
# Anything under /scratch/ stays on the developer's machine: session notes,
# investigation dumps, transient logs, experiment output.  Deliberately ONE
# well-named directory instead of scattered ignore rules.
#
# WARNING - resist the temptation to gitignore parts of docs/ (e.g.
# /docs/dev/): silently-untracked documentation is how project knowledge
# gets lost.  If a doc is worth writing, commit it; if it is throwaway,
# put it in /scratch/.
/scratch/

# =============================================================================
# IDE / Editor / AI
# =============================================================================
.idea/
.vscode/
.ai/
# Claude Code: local state stays ignored, but the project hook config that
# blocks gate-bypass flags is tracked and shared (scripts/hooks/claude_no_bypass.sh).
.claude/*
!.claude/settings.json
.qodo/
.reuse/
.windsurf/
*.iws
*.iml

# =============================================================================
# OS artifacts
# =============================================================================
# Windows
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini
# macOS
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
# Linux
*~

# =============================================================================
# Environment and secrets
# =============================================================================
.env
*.env

# =============================================================================
# Local-only cargo config (personal copies of the committed *.sample.toml)
# =============================================================================
.cargo/macos.toml
.cargo/windows.toml
